Heinz baby food in the US was recalled due to lead concerns, with 14,000 jars affected.
Sara Lee and Oscar Mayer also had recalls for food poisoning outbreaks.
Listeria contamination led to recalls at Thorn Apple Valley and Bil Mar Foods, causing illnesses and deaths.
The USDA urged caution, especially for pregnant women and those with weakened immune systems.
Listeria, found in hot dogs and deli meats, poses serious health risks.
Consumers are advised to cook food thoroughly and practice good hygiene.
IBP recalled ground beef due to E. coli concerns, emphasizing the importance of food safety measures.
